snippet.textDisplay: The Strokes sound like senior year in high school. The point in the year when senioritis dosn't matter anymore, its finally looking like summer, life is new and youthful again after a long period of being overwhelmed at the idea of adulthood and  life. Everything feels timeless, with that passive optimism and idealistic assurance that everything is and always will be ok. So many of their songs evoke a sense of euphoric youth. Can never get tired of them.
